{
  "content": "Routh-Hurwitz is easier than it looks. Just build the array systematically and check the signs in the first column. If all positive the system is stable. Practice with at least 10 examples before the exam."
}

###
# ─── REPLY 5 (top level) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/threads/{{threadId}}/replies
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "content": "State space representation — think of the state vector as capturing everything you need to know about the system at a given moment. The A matrix describes how the state evolves, B is the input effect, C is what you can observe."
}

